[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    39[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe risk profile is comparable to Recipes 3.4 and 3.5 in autoverification-gating consequence terms (the deterioration system is in the alert path of inpatient clinical care; a missed alert is a missed deterioration; an oversensitive system produces alert fatigue that erodes trust and produces missed deteriorations through the back door). The risk profile is elevated relative to Recipes 3.1-3.6 in clinical-safety consequence terms because the system actively contributes to bedside clinical decision-making rather than supporting back-office operations; and elevated in regulatory-and-legal consequence terms because of the FDA CDS / SaMD boundary that the recipe correctly addresses. The recipe correctly addresses the elevated risk in the FDA regulatory determination paragraph, the prospective shadow deployment paragraph, the local validation discussion, the bias-and-equity audit framework paragraph, and the decommissioning-criteria paragraph. The fairness surface area is also distinctive: the recipe explicitly names age bands, sex, race and ethnicity (where structurally captured), insurance status as a useful proxy for SES, unit, service line, primary diagnosis, time of day, day of week as the subgroup dimensions; this is a more comprehensive subgroup taxonomy than any prior recipe.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    40[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    41[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe Honest Take and the Why This Isn't Production-Ready section together are publication-ready voice; the Calibration-Matters-As-Much-As-Discrimination subsection is the recipe's biggest pedagogical contribution. The MEDIUM-finding cluster is an evenly distributed mix of architectural-completeness gaps (A1 idempotency, A2 DLQs, A3 treatment-leakage discipline, A4 cold-start handling, A6 reference-data versioning of feature snapshots, A7 suppression-rule expiry) and PHI/governance backstops (S1 alert payload PHI, S2 subgroup governance). These are the right next-pass priorities; with them addressed, Recipe 3.7 sits at the same publication-ready quality bar as the strongest Chapter 2 and Chapter 3 recipes.[K
