[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     52[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Encryption coverage is complete across every PHI-bearing store: "Customer-managed KMS keys on every PHI-bearing store: DynamoDB, Timestream, S3, OpenSearch, Kinesis, MSK, SageMaker volumes and Feature Store. Key rotation policies set per organizational requirements." Customer-managed-key (rather than AWS-managed default) discipline is the production-correct choice and the recipe states it plainly. TLS 1.2-or-higher in transit is named explicitly.[K
