[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    130[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    131[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhat's Done Well[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    132[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    133[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe four-stage pipeline (streaming ingest and normalization, patient state store, feature engine, scoring service, alert router with tiered destinations and acknowledgment-and-outcome capture, monitoring-and-governance, periodic retraining and threshold review) is the architecturally correct factoring for an inpatient deterioration system. The decision to drive scoring from two paths (DynamoDB Streams for event-driven scoring on high-importance state changes, EventBridge periodic-tick for elapsed-time effects) is the architectural reframe most first-time builders miss, and the recipe is explicit about it.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    134[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Severity tiering as a first-class architectural concern (high tier to pager, medium to charge nurse dashboard, all alerts to EHR banner, end-of-shift report for low tier) with explicit operational distinctions including delta detection (this patient's score just jumped substantially) and tier-escalation gating (same tier on the same patient an hour later doesn't re-page; a tier escalation does) is the architecturally correct factoring.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    135[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The acknowledgment-and-outcome capture path closes the feedback loop with proper label-derivation discipline: "Every alert generates an acknowledgment requirement. Subsequent clinical events (ICU transfer, code blue, sepsis bundle initiation) get linked to the alert as the eventual outcome. ... The combined alert + disposition + outcome record is the labeled data that drives retraining and threshold tuning." This is the operationally-correct labeling path that produces the highest-quality training data; many production deployments skip this and never recover the supervised signal.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    136[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The "monitoring and governance" subsection correctly factors the operational tempo: real-time alert volume dashboards for the operational team, weekly-or-monthly subgroup performance metrics for the model team, alert disposition distributions for the clinical leadership team, retraining cadence as quarterly with shadow-mode-before-promotion. This matches what every senior clinical informatics director would describe.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    137[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m SageMaker Feature Store is correctly identified as the substrate for offline/online consistency with point-in-time correctness for governance and clinical safety review. The point-in-time-correctness framing is exactly right for a regulated workflow where reproducing a past prediction is a CMS-or-Joint-Commission-survey requirement.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    138[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m SageMaker Clarify is correctly positioned for both the fairness reports (subgroup-stratified) and the per-prediction SHAP values that feed the explanation layer. SageMaker Model Monitor is correctly named for data-drift, prediction-drift, and (with labels) quality-drift monitoring.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    139[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The cost estimate is unusually defensible: "$3,000-8,000/month for a single hospital. Compare to typical ICU bed-day costs (often $3,000-5,000/day): preventing one preventable ICU transfer per month covers the infrastructure." The "infrastructure cost is a small fraction; the harder cost is people" framing is operationally accurate and is the right framing for leadership conversations.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    140[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Implementation-time tiers (4-6 months Basic with NEWS2-only, 12-18 months Production-ready with ML model and full governance, 18-36 additional months for variations) are realistic and resist optimism bias. The Production-ready tier explicitly names "shadow-mode prospective validation, full clinical governance committee operating, acknowledgment and outcome capture" as part of the production scope, which is the right discipline.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    141[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Variations and Extensions covers the right adjacent patterns at substantive depth (sepsis-specific, respiratory-failure-specific, post-operative deterioration, pediatric, maternal-fetal, ICU de-escalation/step-down readiness, ED admission decisions, remote patient monitoring, LLM-enhanced explanation, multi-modal, federated learning, closed-loop interventions). The closed-loop framing is appropriately cautious: "Closed-loop systems for clinical interventions raise FDA SaMD considerations meaningfully; deployment requires substantial regulatory and clinical safety work. Most hospitals stay short of full closed-loop and keep the human in the loop for the actual care decisions."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    142[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Why This Isn't Production-Ready section is the densest in any chapter-3 recipe with fifteen substantive bullets covering the right operational disciplines: clinical governance is the entire program; local validation is non-negotiable; prospective shadow deployment; bedside monitor integration; alert routing integration; EHR banner integration is vendor-specific; FDA regulatory determination; bias and equity audit framework; decommissioning criteria; patient-facing transparency; vendor handoffs; disaster recovery and continuity; integration with rapid response and code teams; cross-shift handoffs; research-and-quality-improvement use vs clinical use. Each bullet is tied to a real production concern.[K
