[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    398[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expected Results sample alert payload [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m"narrative"[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m field ("Risk score has increased substantially over the last 4 hours, driven primarily by rising heart rate (76 to 102 bpm), rising respiratory rate (16 to 22), a lactate of 3.2, and temperature trend rising 1.4°C above baseline. Pattern is consistent with early sepsis. Patient is post-op day 2 from colon resection. Blood cultures have been ordered, suggesting bedside team has noted concern. Suggest sepsis bundle evaluation: full set of vitals, repeat lactate, source review, and consideration of empiric antibiotic timing per local sepsis protocol. This is decision support; clinical judgment governs.").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    399[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The sample narrative is well-constructed and demonstrates the constraint boundary the recipe correctly establishes ("cite features, suggest evaluation steps, never recommend specific treatments"). The narrative cites features ("rising heart rate (76 to 102 bpm), rising respiratory rate (16 to 22), a lactate of 3.2, and temperature trend rising 1.4°C above baseline"), suggests evaluation ("Suggest sepsis bundle evaluation: full set of vitals, repeat lactate, source review"), and includes the closing constraint ("This is decision support; clinical judgment governs"). This is the right model output discipline.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    400[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    401[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mBut one phrase ("consideration of empiric antibiotic timing per local sepsis protocol") sits at the boundary between "suggest evaluation steps" and "recommend specific treatments." Empiric antibiotic timing is a treatment recommendation framed as a consideration; the framing is acceptable for the FDA-CDS-exemption posture (transparent reasoning, supports rather than replaces clinician judgment), but a more conservative phrasing would land further from the boundary. Some hospital clinical-governance committees would push back on this specific phrasing on the grounds that "consideration of empiric antibiotic timing" is too close to "start antibiotics now."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    402[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    403[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe recipe correctly identifies this concern in the Bedrock paragraph framing ("never recommend specific treatments"), but the sample narrative includes a near-treatment-recommendation. A reader implementing the explanation layer who uses the sample as a template will produce narratives that drift toward treatment recommendations rather than evaluation suggestions.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    404[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Either (a) tighten the sample narrative to land further from the treatment-recommendation boundary ("Suggest sepsis bundle evaluation: full set of vitals, repeat lactate, source review, and assessment per local sepsis protocol. This is decision support; clinical judgment governs."), or (b) keep the sample as-is but add an inline note in the prose above the sample explaining the boundary: "The phrase 'consideration of empiric antibiotic timing per local sepsis protocol' sits at the constraint boundary; some clinical-governance committees prefer narratives that stop at evaluation suggestions and let the protocol-and-clinician chain handle the timing decision. The exact phrasing is a clinical-governance decision; the LLM constraints are tuned per institution." Option (a) is the smaller editorial change and aligns with the more-conservative posture; option (b) preserves the sample but makes the boundary explicit.[K
