[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    410[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Honest Take's first lesson ("The model is the smaller half of this problem ... I've watched teams spend nine months building a beautiful model and three weeks on alert routing, then wonder why nobody on the floor uses the alerts. It's the alert routing. Build the workflow first, even if it has to be wired to a NEWS2 score initially, and add the better model into it once the workflow is working"); Estimated Implementation Time Basic tier ("NEWS2 calculation engine running on EHR data, single dashboard, basic alert routing to one channel, retrospective performance comparison against existing manual track-and-trigger, monthly governance review | 4-6 months").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    411[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Honest Take's "build the workflow first" lesson is one of the strongest operational-engineer-voice framings in the recipe. The Implementation-Time Tier table's Basic tier embeds exactly this discipline (4-6 months for the NEWS2-engine-and-workflow-only deployment). But the two are not explicitly cross-referenced. A reader reading The Honest Take and being convinced of the discipline does not see that the recipe's own implementation-time tiers reflect it; a reader reading the implementation-time tiers does not see The Honest Take's framing of why the Basic tier looks like it does.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    412[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Either (a) add a one-line cross-reference in The Honest Take's first lesson ("The Basic tier in the Implementation Time table reflects this discipline: a NEWS2-only deployment with full workflow and governance in 4-6 months, before any ML work begins"), or (b) add a one-line note in the Basic tier description ("Equivalent to the workflow-first deployment described in The Honest Take's first lesson"). Option (a) is the smaller editorial change and amplifies The Honest Take's authority by tying it to a concrete implementation tier.[K
